>> title: Cashew Tzatziki
>> cuisine: Mediterranean
>> tags: sauce, vegan, gluten-free, soy-free
>> servings: 8
>> yield: 2 cups
>> storage_days: 7
>> storage_method: refrigerated
>> reheat: Serve cold, stir before using.

-- Cashews must be soaked in boiling water for at least 15 minutes before blending.
-- For a thinner consistency, add more water 1 tablespoon at a time.

Blend soaked @raw cashews{1%cup}(soaked in boiling water 15+ minutes, drained), @water{1/2%cup}, @fresh lemon juice{2%tbsp}, @garlic{1%clove}, and @kosher salt{1/2%tsp} in #high-powered blender{} until completely smooth, ~{1-2%minutes}. Scrape down sides as needed.

Transfer to #bowl{}. Stir in @cucumber{1/2}(medium, seeded and finely diced, about 3/4 cup), @fresh dill{2%tbsp}(chopped), @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and @black pepper{}(freshly cracked, to taste).

Taste and adjust lemon/salt.

Store in #jar{} in refrigerator. Stir before using.

-- Used in: Mediterranean bowls, Greek salad, mezze plate, grain bowls, as a dip
